13:["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginBottom":"1rem","lineHeight":1.7},"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Vienna & Oakton:"}]," Deck replacements on 1980s-1990s colonials, screened porch additions, and pergola installations. Many homes here have original wood decks that are now 25-30 years old — prime candidates for composite upgrades."]}]
14:["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginBottom":"1rem","lineHeight":1.7},"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Reston & Herndon:"}]," Reston Association-approved composite builds, townhome deck/patio combos, and elevated deck designs for wooded lots with grade changes. We have extensive experience with Reston's architectural review requirements."]}]
15:["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginBottom":"1rem","lineHeight":1.7},"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Burke, Springfield & Lorton:"}]," Family-oriented deck builds with integrated lighting, stair systems, and multi-level designs for sloped lots. Budget-friendly Trex Enhance projects are popular here at $30-$50/sqft."]}]
16:["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginBottom":"2rem","lineHeight":1.7},"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Centreville & Chantilly:"}]," Full deck replacements, composite resurfacing, and fence packages. HOA communities like Virginia Run and Sully Station have specific requirements we know well."]}]
